Television actor Davies Mwabili, popularly known as Inspekta Mwala, is yet again on the spot after he hit and killed a pedestrian in Kaloleni, Kilifi County. Kilifi police commander Patrick Okeri said Mr Mwabili knocked down a 35-year-old man killing him on the spot on Monday night. The actor was driving from Kaloleni town on Mazeras Highway when he hit the man who was crossing the road, the police boss said. Mr Okeri said Mr Mwabili is out on police bail and the vehicle he was driving at the time of the crash, a Toyota Axio, is being detained at Kaloleni Police Station. The police boss said the body of the pedestrian was taken to Coast General Hospital Mortuary in Mombasa.  